values:
Y'know...  I know it's horrible to say, but I'm really glad mom and granny are out of town for a week.  Dad and I get along smashingly when we're not being nagged 24/7.  Yesterday was great.  Slept in while dad was at work.  Took the dog to get him cleaned and de-stinkified.  After dad got home, we picked up the dog and ate a mediocre dinner at Hard Times Cafe.  Since the weather was BEAUTIFUL, we ate outside on the patio.  Talked nerd to each other...  talked movies, motorcylces, cars, etc.  It was thoroughly enjoyable.  Then we drove out to Georgetown, this nifty place on the waterfront in the District.  Walked around, checking out boats, looking at the stores.  Had a chai latte.  Went to Barnes & Noble and marveled at their woefully understocked manga section.  Then we went to see Matrix Reloaded.  I hadn't been looking forward to seeing it, but dad really wanted to, so I wanted to be nice and go with him.  I was impressed.  Really, truly impressed.  It was remarkably better than the first one.  It really made steps towards being a real sci-fi, instead of an overstated action movie with a decent plot.  I could've done without the extended rave scene in Zion.  There were definitely a few extraneous scenes in the movie.  But all in all, I thought it was great...  ^_^;;; Please, no "I told you so"s...  I still dislike the first one just as much as I did before.  But I give Reloaded a 4 out of 5, definitely ^_^;

Anyways, I gotta get going.  I have episodes of Gravitation to download, and a DDR pad to finish.  I'd like to give a shout out to my new roomie for next semester, Kristi...  ^_^; She's pretty cool.  I think we'll get on okay next semester.  Anyways...

Peace Out, and Blessed Be...
